messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, we're, um, at the corner of 119 and County Road 1. We just saw a plane go down.
Where exactly?
The corner of 119 and County Road 1.
Right there in the intersection?
Yes.
Okay, what direction from McLean?
I'm facing south right now. It's in the south field on that intersection.
Did you see any smoke or flames?
No, but we heard it go boom. We don't see any smoke or flames yet.
Did you witness it go down?
Yes.
What's your name?
Sabrina.
Can I get a phone number, please?
What kind of plane was it, do you think?
It looks just a white, maybe a two-seater.
Have you pulled over? Can you see it?
I'm at work on lunch right now. We could see it go down from across where we're at.
Alright, thank you very much. We're on our way.
Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, Longmont, Colorado, about three miles to the south of Union Reservoir. A plane just crashed.
Okay, you said three miles south of Union Reservoir?
Yeah, we're on 1640 Bluefield. I'm sitting on my porch and it spiraled down below the treetops and I heard the impact.
Okay. We actually have other calls and we're going to head that way.
Alright, very good. Thanks.
Thank you. Bye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hi, I'm calling from Highway 119 and County Road 1.
Okay, is this about the plane?
It is.
Are you actually close enough to where the plane crashed?
Yeah, it crashed a couple hundred feet in front of me as I was driving.
Have you seen anyone get out of the plane?
I have not.
I just want to confirm it was a small white plane, correct?
Yes.
And is it southeast of your location?
No, it's north of me. A police officer just showed up.
Okay, I'll let you go. Should I go talk to him about what I saw?
Yes, go ahead and contact them. They'll probably be going to the plane crash first.
Alright, thank you.
Okay, thank you. Bye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, are you calling about the plane crash?
We do have it, sir, but did you witness it?
I did see it go down, but I didn't see it crash.
What's your name?
Brian Larche.
Thank you very much. What's a phone number you can be reached at?
Can you tell me where you saw it go down?
I was at the country club, and it looks like it is right behind some houses there.
Is it to the north?
South of 119 and west of the county line.
So southwest corner?
Yes, but more behind those houses there.
Do you think it's behind Walmart to the south of Walmart?
It's definitely quite a bit further west of Walmart.
So it's south and west?
Yes.
Did you see any smoke or flames?
I just saw some dust come up. I definitely heard it hit.
Okay, sir, thank you very much. We're on our way.
Alright, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, this is the city of Longmont over at Public Works. There's been a plane crash in our area.
Okay, what's the address?
375 St. Vrain Road.
Hold on for me just one moment.
Dispatch, this is Beth.
Hey Beth, it's Jan from Estes. I heard about a Cessna that went down.
Yes, ma'am, but I'm not able to take your call right now. I believe we've got a second plane crash. You'll need to call back, I'm sorry.
Are you with what agency?
I'm with Estes. My sergeant's son is up in a Cessna.
I'm sorry, I'm working two plane crashes right now. Please call back in a few.
No worries. Alright, bye.
Thanks for holding. Are you calling about a plane crash at the airport?
Yes.
Were you involved?
No, I'm an employee.
Okay, you're an employee? Where did it crash?
Into the back of our yard on the south side of our facility.
What's the address?
375 South Airport.
Any injuries?
Yes, there's a lady. They pulled her out of the plane. She's conscious.
Are you with her now?
No.
Did you witness it?
I did not.
Alright, we're on our way, okay?
Thank you.
Uh-huh, bye-bye.
